Review: Dinner is better than brunch, the prosciutto sandwich is a pass but the pizzas are all good, well cooked.
one of the best friend chicken sandwiches i’ve ever had. their homemade sweet and sour sauce was incredible. nice mom and pop shop.
The wings were incredible and the oysters had this delicious spicy chimichurri/chutney that had amazing depth of flavor. Cocktails were alright but it’s well worth it during happy hour.

So overrated, the carne asada was flavorful but it’s way overpriced and the burrito is tiny, you also need to pay extra for basics in a burrito. El Rancho Grande is a lot better and cheaper and is close by, much better option.
Bagels were nothing special but the smoked fish was delicious and the scallion cream cheese also great. The egg, salmon, and pastrami bagel was 8/10, will be back for a hungover breakfast.
Chicken was a little dry, generous portions but nothing to rave about. Nice outdoor seating, decent lunch spot in downtown pleasanton but there are better spots around.
Great sake, great ambiance, great bartenders all in a no-frills non-pretentious environment
The iced coffee is named “The Best Iced Coffee” and I’d give it a 7/10, pretty solid
Best slice I’ve had in brooklyn 9/10
Best lamb shawarma in Pleasanton, has been for 10+ years
